<h2 style="font-size: 22px;">Pratt Institute</h2>
<strong>Brooklyn, NY</strong>

<div class="infolines">
    <div class="row-fluid">
        <div class="span10">Offers credit for AP Exams</div>
        <div class="span2 alignRight">
                <div class="short-status-green">Yes</div>
        </div>
    </div>    
    <div class="row-fluid">
        <div class="span10">Offers placement into higher-level courses for AP Exams</div>
        <div class="span2 alignRight">
                <div class="short-status-green">Yes</div>
        </div>
    </div>    
</div>


<p>
    <strong>From the college:</strong>
    <i>AP ENG LANG/COMP score of 4 or 5, the student receives credit for ENGL 101 (3-credits.) 
A score of 4 or 5 on the following tests are awarded the courses listed below. All courses listed are 3 credits at Pratt. 
Calculus AB :=Math 151
Calculus BC = Math 151
Chemistry= Sci 170   
Environmental Science= Sci 177
Physics B= Sci 170
Electricity and Magnetism= Sci 170
Mechanics= Sci 170
Biology= Sci 170
Statistics= 151
Score of 4 or 5 on the AP Art History exam are given credit for the Pratt course HA 115 - 3 credits.
*Note: A student achieving an AP score of 3 in the History of Art and/or Design will have the option to be interviewed by the chairperson of the department to determine sufficient mastery of course material.</i>
    <br/>
    For more information, <a href="http://www.pratt.edu/admissions/applying/applying_undergrad/ug_application_requirements/freshmen/" target="_blank" title="Opens a new window">view the credit policy on this college's website</a>.
</p>

 <p class="box-padding-3">
    Additional restrictions and requirements may apply to the policy listed below. For more detailed information, visit the college's AP policy on the Web or contact the college directly.
 </p>

